PPT to Beamer Skill -- third-party notices
==========================================

This skill repository contains no third-party assets.  It encodes a
methodology (in `SKILL.md`) that Claude uses to read PowerPoint
templates and generate Beamer themes; the methodology is original work
licensed under MIT (see `LICENSE`).

When the skill is *applied* to a PowerPoint template, the resulting
Beamer-theme folder will typically include:

  * The LaTeX code (`.sty`, `.tex`, `README.md`) -- MIT-licensable by
    the user; the skill imposes no restrictions on derivative work.

  * Brand assets (logo PNGs, wordmarks, emblems) copied from the input
    PowerPoint template or supplied separately by the user.  These
    remain the intellectual property and trademarks of the originating
    institution; the skill does NOT relicense them.

  * A generated `NOTICE` file in the output folder explaining the
    licensing of the produced theme.

The skill embeds the following template into every generated `NOTICE`
file (parameterised with the institution's name).  Users of the
generated theme are expected to abide by the institution's brand-use
guidelines when publishing or sharing the resulting deck.

